  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large skillet, melt the pork fat over medium heat.",
    "Add the mascarpone cheese and stir until smooth.",
    "Add the granulated sugar, lemon juice, blueberries, raspberries, and strawberries. Cook for 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in the salted almonds, orange zest, and smoked paprika.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Dot the top with the unsalted butter.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the filling is set and the top is lightly golden.",
    "Garnish with fresh mint leaves and serve warm."
